  health                    Run health check (also: doctor)
  status                    Show yadm status + n0dm backup info
  update                    Check for and install n0dm updates
  mergetool                 Launch configured merge tool for conflicts

${BOLD}Yadm Passthrough Commands (ALL native commands work):${RESET}
  add, commit, push, pull, merge, branch, remote, checkout
  reset, restore, clean, config, log, diff, enter, alt, encrypt, decrypt
  bootstrap, help, version, list, status
  → All other commands pass directly to yadm unchanged

${BOLD}Command Conflict Resolution:${RESET}
  • 'restore': n0dm restore = backup restore | yadm restore = git restore
    → Use 'n0dm yadm-restore' to access native yadm restore
  • 'list': Passes through to yadm list + shows brief backup hint
  • 'status': Shows yadm status first, then appends n0dm backup info

${BOLD}Options (for sync):${RESET}
  --no-backup               Skip smart backup check
  --dry-run                 Show what would be done
  --yes                     Auto-confirm prompts (for automation)
  --verbose                 Show detailed sync analysis
  --force                   Force push (overwrite remote on first sync)
  --safe                    Abort on any error, send notifications
  (no message)              Auto-generates commit message from git diff

${BOLD}Environment Variables:${RESET}
  N0DM_MAX_BACKUPS          Max backups to keep (default: 10)
  N0DM_BACKUP_RETENTION     Days to retain backups (default: 30)
  N0DM_YES                  Set to 'true' for non-interactive mode

${BOLD}Smart Backup Logic:${RESET}
  • Backup created ONLY if tracked files changed since last backup
  • First sync always creates backup (no previous state)
  • Retention policy prevents backup pollution automatically
  • Safety backup always created before 'restore' regardless of smart logic

${BOLD}Examples:${RESET}
  n0dm init                              # Initialize yadm repo
  n0dm clone noeltz/n0ctachiri          # Clone from GitHub (short format)
  n0dm clone noeltz/n0ctachiri -f      # Force clone (overwrite local)
  n0dm track ~/.bashrc                   # Add file to tracking
  n0dm untrack ~/.cache/file             # Remove from tracking (keep file)
  n0dm sync                              # Safe sync (auto-generates commit message)
  n0dm sync "Update config"              # Safe sync with custom message
  n0dm sync --dry-run                    # Preview changes
  n0dm schedule hourly                   # Enable hourly auto-sync
  n0dm schedule daily                    # Enable daily auto-sync
  n0dm schedule off                      # Disable auto-sync
  n0dm backup "before-vim-upgrade"       # Manual backup
  n0dm backups                           # List all backups
  n0dm restore 20260223_143022_pre-sync  # Restore from backup
  n0dm commit -m "msg"                   # Commit changes
  n0dm push                              # Push to GitHub
  n0dm list                              # List tracked files
  n0dm status                            # Enhanced status
  n0dm health                            # Run health check
  n0dm sync --safe --yes                 # Safe auto-sync with notifications
  n0dm update                            # Self-update n0dm
  n0dm yadm-restore .bashrc              # Access native yadm restore

${BOLD}Automation:${RESET}
